  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1339",
  "title": "Change props auto documentation to simple jsDoc annotations",
  "body": "The current props auto documentation tries to infer most of the props documentation from PropTypes definitions by running the code into webpack/babel and then using somehow complex code from a custom loader.\n\nUnfortunately what started as a good idea is a pain to understand, maintain and update.\nThe current state is that the prop generation is buggy and misses important informations, as seen in #1302.\n\nWe could try to fix it but given what's coming next #1303 and #1338, let's make it simple right now.\n\n**I propose** to move everything to very simple jsDoc that will be parseable, don't fear not being 100% DRY. Not being DRY is good if it helps a lot our own documentation flow and understanding of our own documentation generation.\n\nLet's start with something boring but exhaustive and effectiveness that will then give us some time to think about how to really make it better/DRY.\n\n@bobylito I know you worked heavily with jsDoc, if you are up to trying this and removing most of the \"plugins/inlineProps\" files, go\n\nThe plan:\n- [x] POC the doc on Hits\n- [x] Improve the metalsmith jsDoc plugin to be able to read mutliple files\n- [x] Integrate the plugin to generate pages for the Hits component and connect HOC\n- [ ] Reproduce for all the other widgets\n- [ ] Add to every widgets the live example\n",
  "created_at": "2016-09-26T20:20:39Z",
